[1] Case updates
- Sat 2 Mar 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans. abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=ec0e947de0

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 1 Mar 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 890, of which 825 are confirmed, and 65 are probable. In total, there have been 559 deaths (494 among confirmed and 65 in probable cases) and 302 people have recovered.
- 172 suspected cases under investigation;
- 2 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Katwa and 1 in Mandima;
- 2 new confirmed cases deaths: 1 community death in Katwa; 1 case death confirmed at Katwa CT.

News of the response
--------------------
Vaccination
Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 84 948 people have been vaccinated [see numbers per location at URL above].

--
