******
[3] Consequences and follow-up of attacks
Date: Thu 28 Feb 2019
Source: Actualite [online translation, abridged, edited]
https://actualite.cd/2019/02/28/rdc-un-policier-tue-dans-lattaque-contre-un-centre-de-traitement-debola-butembo


A police officer was killed on Wed 27 Feb 2019 in the evening, during an attack by gunmen on another Ebola treatment center (ETC) in Butembo town. The attackers set fire to the center, which housed some 30 patients, police said.

Colonel Richard Mbambi, commander of the police in Butembo, indicates that the policeman killed was committed to the protection of the ETC, erected in the concession of the Institute of Agricultural and Veterinary Techniques (ITAV), Lumumba district, in the commune of Kimemi, and assigned to the organization MSF. Police authorities attribute the attack to the militia Mai-Mai Mazembe. They also report material damage, namely a vehicle, 7 motorcycles, and a generator set on fire.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

